de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.jcomparser.xml

Class Fragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.jcomparser.xml.Fragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeserialisable, IPersistable

    public class Fragment
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDeserialisable, IPersistable
    Represents a Fragment of the XML-Model. It implements the IDeserialisable interface, which allows to initialize a fragment Object from an XML and the IPersistable Interface, which allows to save the Object to the Database.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Fragment()
      This constructor is only used for testcases as a connection to the server is not needed therefore.
      Fragment(java.lang.String serverURL)
      Sets the processeditorServerUrl which is needed for connecting to the server in order to get the XML-files for the fragments.
